rm(list=ls())
library(readxl)
setwd('C:/Users/Adam/Desktop/Data Analytics files/Project')

myData <- read.csv('movie_metadata.csv')

options(scipen= 999)


### box and whisker outliers
boxplot(myData$director_facebook_likes, main = "Director Facebook Likes",horizontal = TRUE, ylim=c(0,1000), col = 'dark red')

boxplot(myData$actor_1_facebook_likes, main = "Lead Actor FB likes", horizontal = TRUE, ylim =c(0,30000), col = 'aquamarine' )

boxplot(myData$imdb_score, main = "IMDB Score", horizontal = TRUE, col='azure')

boxplot(myData$budget, main= "Budget", horizontal = TRUE, ylim = c(0, 150000000), col='coral')

boxplot(myData$num_critic_for_reviews, main = "Number of Critic reviews per movie",  horizontal = TRUE, col='cadetblue')

boxplot(myData$duration, main= "Movie Duration", horizontal = TRUE, ylim =c(0,511), col = 'gold1')

boxplot(myData$gross, main = "Gross",  horizontal = TRUE, col='blue')

#outliersDirector <- boxplot(myData$director_facebook_likes)$out; outliersDirector
#outliersActor <- boxplot(myData$actor_1_facebook_likes)$out; outlieractor


### Q. MLR scatter  Gross on IMDB Score

plot(myData$gross~myData$imdb_score, main = 'Imdb Score vs Gross Revenue',
     xlab = "IMBD Score", ylab = "Gross Revenue",col='red', pch = 20, 
     xlim= c(1,10), ylim= c(0, 800000000))

### Q. MLR scatter IMBDscore on director facebook likes 

plot(myData$director_facebook_likes~myData$imdb_score, main = 'Imdb score vs Director Facebook Likes',
     xlab = "IMBD Score", ylab = "Director likes", col= "chartreuse4", pch = 20, 
     xlim= c(1,10), ylim= c(0, 23000))

### Q, MLR scatter IMBDscore on actor facebook likes

plot(myData$actor_1_facebook_likes~myData$imdb_score, main = 'Imdb score vs Lead Actor facebook Likes',
     xlab = "IMBD Score", ylab = "Actor facebook facebook",col = "aquamarine4", pch = 20, 
     xlim= c(1,10), ylim= c(0, 30000))
